<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>With just under two weeks until the international transfer window closes on October 5, clubs across Europe are looking to bring in flesh blood as the 2020-21 season starts to get going. </p>

<p>Chris Smalling, who has become surplus to requirements at Manchester United, will hope to resolve his future in the coming weeks, with the defender calling for a permanent return to Roma where he spent last season on loan.</p>

<p>Meanwhile, Chelsea have drawn up plans to trim their squad after significant summer investment. Kepa Arrizabalaga, Antonio Rudiger and Ruben Loftus-Cheek are among the players who could be sold.</p>

<p>Sportsmail will provide live updates of the summer transfer window including permnanent signings, loan deals and latest negotiations across the Premier League and European clubs. </p>

<p>Host commentator</p>

<p>Derby have signed Bobby Duncan from Fiorentina on a three-year deal. </p>

<p>The former Liverpool and Manchester City prospect has represented England at youth international level.</p>

<p>🇮🇹🛬🏴󠁧󠁢󠁥󠁮󠁧󠁿<?php echo e('@'); ?>England youth international forward, <?php echo e('@'); ?>bobbyduncan999, joins Derby County on a three-year deal from <?php echo e('@'); ?>acffiorentina ✍️#DCFC</p>

<p>Mario Balotelli is poised to join Genoa from Brescia on a one-year deal.</p>

<p>Balotelli suffered relegation to Serie B with Brescia last season, scoring five goals in 19 league appearances.</p>

<p>Aston Villa coach John Terry says the club had no option but to spend big after narrowly avoiding Premier League relegation. </p>

<p>The Villans have spent approximately £86million this summer, including a club-record deal for striker Ollie Watkins.</p>

<p>Fulham defender Jerome Opoku has joined League One Plymouth Argyle until January 2021.</p>

<p>The 21-year-old made 25 appearances while on loan at Accrington Stanley last season.</p>

<p>All the best for the next few months at <?php echo e('@'); ?>Only1Argyle, Jerome! 👊#FFC</p>

<p>Atletico Madrid have announced the £5.5million signing of Luis Suarez on a two-year deal. </p>

<p>The Uruguayan has left Barcelona after six trophy-laden years in which he became the club's third-highest scorer of all time..</p>

<p>Everton midfielder Dennis Adeniran has joined Championship club Wycombe Wanderers on a season-long loan. </p>

<p>The 21-year-old is yet to make a senior appearance for the Toffees but has represented England at youth international level</p>

